===Alternative spellings===
:'''[[ix-nay]]'''

===Etymology===
[[Pig Latin]] version of [[nix]]; possibly the only Pig Latin phrase to enter common English besides [[amscray]].  Ixnay and amscray were used widely in "The Three Stooges" shorts, possibly the main source of popularizing the words.

